  "original_title": "\u0dad\u0dc0\u0dad\u0dca 198\u0d9a\u0dca \u0d9a\u0ddc\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0da7 - \u0db8\u0dda \u0dc0\u0dc3\u0dbb\u0dda 2105\u0d9a\u0dca \u0d9a\u0ddc\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0da7 \u0d9c\u0dd2\u0dc4\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Another 198 to Korea - 2105 have gone to Korea this year",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "According to the Memorandum of Understanding between the Government of Sri Lanka and the Government of South Korea, under the program of providing jobs to Sri Lankan workers in South Korea, 2105 people have left this notice since January 2022, according to the Foreign Employment Bureau of Sri Lanka.",
        "Most of them have passed the Korean Language Proficiency Test under the normal method and the number is 1611.",
        "After working continuously in Korea for 04 years and 10 months, after returning to Sri Lanka and receiving a service contract from the previous company, 299 people have left for work in Korea.",
        "195 people have left for jobs after passing the computer related exam. Meanwhile, the highest number of workers who have left for Korean jobs from January to now, 676 people, left in June.",
        "As a result of the discussions held by the Minister of Labor and Foreign Employment Mr. Manusha Nanayakkara, the Korean Department of Human Resources and the higher officials of the Sri Lanka Foreign Employment Bureau in order to speed up the program of sending more Sri Lankan workers for Korean jobs, more employment contracts are being received.",
        "Meanwhile, the 723rd group leaving for Korean work left the island yesterday, the group of 34 people who left yesterday afternoon on SriLankan Airlines flight UL 308 and the 164 people who left last night on SriLankan Airlines flight UL 470. left"
      ],
